    "title": "Indian Oil Corporation is Hiring: Quality Control Engineer (Mid-Level)",
    "description": "Indian Oil Corporation is actively seeking a talented and motivated Quality Control Engineer to join our dynamic team in Indore. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Indian Oil Corporation:\nIndian Oil Corporation is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Manage raw material procurement and inventory levels\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in Statistical Process Control\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Indore, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Indian Oil Corporation!",
